"value":0.13,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.13\u00d7, interest cover 19.7\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":13.88,"unit":"% YoY","status":"ok","read":"Profit up 14% YoY \u2014 modest.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":56.3,"pe_percentile":42.0,"median_pe":58.6,"earnings_yield_pct":1.78,"pb":9.22,"ev_ebitda":36.11,"quality_score":76.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":53.7,"peg":1.05,"cheapness":{"status":"ok","read":"P/E at the 42-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 mid-range vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 56.3\u00d7 earnings for ~54% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22481.05\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds. This PEG divides TTM P/E by TRAILING 5-year annual PAT CAGR (endpoint-to-endpoint) \u2014 a time-axis mismatch vs the textbook FORWARD-EPS PEG, and one abnormal base/terminal year distorts the CAGR. A rough trailing valuation-vs-growth gauge, not a precise forward PEG.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isol